---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Trademark Policy - Barbacane" description="Barbacane trademark usage guidelines and policy.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-invert">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
          <span class="text-gradient">Trademark Policy</span>
        </h1>

        <div class="text-foreground-muted space-y-6">
          <p>
            "Barbacane" is a trademark. While our software is open source under the Apache 2.0
            license, the Barbacane name and logo are protected to ensure quality and prevent confusion.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mt-12 mb-4">Permitted uses</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
            <li>Referring to Barbacane software in documentation, articles, and talks</li>
            <li>Stating compatibility or integration with Barbacane (e.g., "Works with Barbacane")</li>
            <li>Attribution when distributing unmodified Barbacane software</li>
            <li>Using "Built with Barbacane" or similar factual statements</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mt-12 mb-4">Restricted uses</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
            <li>Using "Barbacane" in product or company names</li>
            <li>Using the Barbacane logo in advertising without permission</li>
            <li>Implying endorsement or official affiliation</li>
            <li>Using the marks in ways that could cause confusion about the source</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mt-12 mb-4">Questions?</h2>
          <p>
            If you're unsure about a specific use, please contact us at{' '}
            <a href="mailto:contact@barbacane.dev" class="text-primary hover:underline">
              contact@barbacane.dev
            </a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
